      "text": [
        " اَلرَّجُلِ يَؤُمُّ اَلنِّسَاءَ لَيْسَ مَعَهُنَّ رَجُلٌ فِي اَلْفَرِيضَةِ قَالَ «نَعَمْ وَ إِنْ كَانَ مَعَهُ صَبِيٌّ فَلْيَقُمْ إِلَى جَانِبِهِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1168 - Ibrahim ibn Maymun narrated from Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) regarding a man leading women in the obligatory prayer, with no other man present.\nImam (as) said: \"Yes, he may lead them, and if there is a boy present, he should stand beside him.\""
        ]
      }
